                "description": {
                    "value": "<p>Toxic materials and churning rubbish within the filth fire's body explode in one of three ways. The filth fire chooses the effect, but it can't make the same choice twice in a row.</p><ul><li>Fiery Beam (evocation, fire, primal) The filth fire expels a 30-foot line of flame that deals [[/r 3d6 # fire damage]] fire damage with a <span data-pf2-check=\"reflex\" data-pf2-dc=\"21\" data-pf2-traits=\"evocation,fire,primal,damaging-effect\" data-pf2-label=\"Noxious Burst DC\" data-pf2-show-dc=\"gm\">basic Reflex</span> save.</li><li>Shrapnel Blast (evocation, primal) The filth fire shoots jagged rubbish out in a 5-foot emanation that deals [[/r 2d12 # piercing damage]] piercing damage with a <span data-pf2-check=\"reflex\" data-pf2-dc=\"21\" data-pf2-traits=\"evocation,primal,damaging-effect\" data-pf2-label=\"Noxious Burst DC\" data-pf2-show-dc=\"gm\">basic Reflex</span> save.</li><li>Toxic Fumes (evocation, poison, primal) The filth fire belches a 15-foot cone of toxic smoke that deals [[/r 2d6 # poison damage]] poison damage (<span data-pf2-check=\"fortitude\" data-pf2-dc=\"21\" data-pf2-traits=\"evocation,primal,poison,damaging-effect\" data-pf2-label=\"Noxious Burst DC\" data-pf2-show-dc=\"gm\">basic Fortitude</span> save). A creature that fails is also @Compendium[pf2e.conditionitems.Sickened]{Sickened} 1 (or sickened 2 on a critical failure).</li></ul>"
